  "prompt": "What are Bernie Sanders' economic policy views?",
  "response": "Bernie Sanders, the United States senator from Vermont, is known for his progressive economic policy views, which he describes as democratic socialism. Some of the key elements of his economic policy proposals include:\n\n1. Wealth and Income Inequality: Sanders believes that the level of wealth and income inequality in the U.S. is too high and unsustainable. He has proposed policies such as increasing the minimum wage, raising taxes on the wealthy, and breaking up large banks to address these issues.\n\n2. Healthcare: Sanders is a strong proponent of a single-payer healthcare system, often referred to as \"Medicare for All,\" which would provide universal coverage and be funded by the government.\n\n3. Education: Sanders advocates for free tuition at public colleges and universities, as well as the cancellation of all student debt.\n\n4. Labor: Sanders is a strong supporter of workers' rights and has proposed policies such as strengthening unions, expanding collective bargaining rights, and increasing the minimum wage.\n\n5. Climate Change: Sanders has proposed a \"Green New Deal,\" which would involve a massive investment in renewable energy and other measures to combat climate change.\n\n6. Taxation: Sanders has proposed a number of tax reforms, including raising taxes on the wealthy and corporations, closing tax loopholes, and implementing a wealth tax on the ultra-rich.\n\n7. Trade: Sanders is a critic of many free trade agreements, arguing that they have led to job losses in the U.S. and a race to the bottom in terms of wages and working conditions. He has proposed renegotiating these agreements to include stronger labor and environmental protections.",
